Library Management System (Java)

Overview
A console-based Library Management System built using Java.
It allows managing books, members, issuing/returning books, and persistent storage using file handling.

->Features
    Add / remove books
    Add / remove members
    Issue and return books
    Search books by title/author
    View all books and issued books
    Persistent storage using .txt files
    Sorting and filtering using Java Streams

->Tech Used
    Java
    OOP (Encapsulation, Abstraction)
    Collections (HashMap, List)
    File Handling (BufferedReader, BufferedWriter)
    Java Streams

->How to Run
    Clone the repository
    Open in IDE (IntelliJ / Eclipse)
    Run Main.java
    Use menu options

